Baylor’s LaQuan McGowan became a national sensation last season when the 410-pounder scored a touchdown in the Cotton Bowl, and over the offseason the former lineman transitioned to tight end. McGowan was listed at 390 pounds last year, but the extra weight didn’t stop him from juking a Kansas defender on the way to the endzone Saturday. 
Fun fact: The first word in McGowan’s bio on Baylor’s website is “enormous.” Read or Share this story: http://on.wtsp.com/1RAbMum TOP VIDEOS
